<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4353] rename solr/example/contexts/solr.xml to reduce &quot;solr.xml&quot; confusion</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4353</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve occasionally seen people get confused about editing the &quot;example solr.xml file&quot; because in addition to the &quot;real&quot; solr.xml file for configuring solr, they also find the jetty context file which is named &quot;solr.xml&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unlike tomcat, where the context descriptor file name determines the webapp path, jetty doesn&apos;t care what the file name is &amp;#8211; it just globs up all the context files and looks at the &quot;contextPath&quot; properties on the WebAppContext objects in those files.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
